post_text:
Mayor Marl, Police Chief Hart to host back-to-school event at Mickey’s Dairy Twist!

SALINE, MI – Mayor Brian Marl and Police Chief Hart announced a back-to-school event at Mickey’s Dairy Twist, scheduled for Thursday, August 27. “It has been a challenging year and an unorthodox summer,” said Mayor Marl. “But with the start of school fast approaching, we wanted to take an opportunity to congratulate our students on
their academic achievements and wish them the very best as they begin the 2020-2021 school year.”

The back-to-school ice cream event will be held on:
Thursday, August 27th
2-4 PM
Mickey’s Dairy Twist
751 West Michigan Avenue
Saline, MI 48176
The event is free, and open to all students in the Saline Area School district, ice cream will be
provided courtesy of Mayor Marl & Police Chief Hart.

Participants should bring masks and
engage in social distancing for the duration of the event.

SCOTGRADEN.COM

shared_text:
University of Michigan Depression Center
April 21 at 11:23 AM ·

Three student photographers in the Peer-to-Peer (P2P) program joined the Photovoice project.

Caroline Thomas, Tess Carichner and Naomi Alvarado spearheaded the storytelling.

See the exhibit: http://michmed.org/o43Kq 📸

These three represent Ann Arbor Public Schools, Saline Area Schools, and Washtenaw Intermediate School District.

SAS MEAL PROGRAM: IMPORTANT UPDATE!

Starting now, families will need to sign up for meals on a weekly basis. The window to request meals for the following week will open on Friday at 12:00 p.m., and close on Monday at 12:00 p.m. When you sign up, you are now accounted for the following Tuesday and Friday for meal pickup. The pickup process, location, days and times will stay the same.

ANYONE can receive meals (18 and under, or 26 and under with special needs).

Meal request for the week of April 20th, 2020, is now open - click here: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSchw4fibv3Vmms1cpu_z4wyFTN8SpzOC3NTl4FefvoflXn17A/viewform
